 data←GenerateTestData n;_NotFixedKeys;_Unique;event;event_type;fixed_keys;keywords;lipsum;organisation;person;person_names;presentation;presentation_media;presentation_type;presentation_video;presenter;stems;thing_names;videos;youtube_video
⍝ Insert dummy data into the database for testing
⍝ First tests considered:
⍝ - /videos?search= should return all videos with matching terms
⍝ - /videos?presenter=p_name should return all videos by presenter p_name
⍝ - /videos?search=p_name       should include videos by presenter p_name
⍝ FIXME this is not comprehensive. Fields essential to the video library are used, but many are not.

⍝ Start by generating joined data and deconstructing it into the normalised database, then loop over each table and insert.

⍝ CONFIG
 keywords←GENERATE.keywords
 stems←GENERATE.stemmable[;2]
 person_names←'Geoff' 'Streeter' 'John' 'Scholes' 'Iverson' 'Dolor' 'Fugiat' 'Orange' 'Rich' 'Park' 'Jada' 'Andrade' 'Andy' 'Karen' 'Fiona' 'Jason' 'Peter' 'Silas'
 thing_names←'APL' 'Meeting' 'Seeds' 'Conference' 'Dyalog' 'Alpha' 'Omega'
 lipsum←GENERATE.lipsum

⍝ GENERATE
 ⎕RL←42
 _Unique←{⍺←⊢ ⋄ ∧/≠r←⍺ ⍺⍺ ⍵:r ⋄ ⍺ ∇ ⍵}

⍝ Use ⎕DF to give each namespace a name that can be used to look up into SQL table metadata
 event_type←(
     type:(vocab:keywords ⋄ max:1)GENERATE.Name n
     description:(vocab:lipsum ⋄ max:65535)GENERATE.Text n
     url_slug:GENERATE.URL _Unique n
 )
 event_type.⎕DF'event_type'

 event←()
 event.title←(vocab:thing_names ⋄ max:3)GENERATE.Name n
 event.(start end)←GENERATE.DateTime¨2⍴n
 event.type_id←?n⍴n
 event.url_slug←'-'@(' '∘=)¨¯1 ⎕C event.title
 event.url_slug,¨←'-',∘⍕¨⍳n
 event.⎕DF'event'
 example_event←⊃event.url_slug   ⍝ Use example_event in DummyData.TestGETVideos_EventShortname

 organisation←()
 organisation.name←(vocab:thing_names ⋄ max:2)GENERATE.Name n
 organisation.name,¨←'-',∘⍕¨⍳n
 organisation.⎕DF'organisation'

 person←()
 person.name←(vocab:person_names ⋄ max:3)GENERATE.Name n
 person.organisation_id←?n⍴n
 person.⎕DF'person'

 presentation_type←(type:(⊂?n⍴≢keywords)⌷keywords)
 presentation_type.⎕DF'presentation_type'

 presentation←()
 presentation.event_id←?n⍴n-1   ⍝ events 1..n-1 only; event n guaranteed no presentations → has_videos=0
 presentation.event_id[⍳6]←1    ⍝ presentation 1 → event 1; combined with fixed_keys, event 1 has has_videos=1
 presentation.code←n⍴⊂''
 _←{presentation.code[⍵]←⍕¨⍳≢⍵}⌸presentation.event_id   ⍝ Unique codes within each event
 presentation.title←stems
 presentation.title,←(vocab:lipsum ⋄ max:30)GENERATE.Text n-≢stems
 presentation.title[1],←⊂' dolor'   ⍝ Ensure a keyword is present in search results
 presentation.type_id←?n⍴n
 presentation.description←(vocab:lipsum ⋄ max:65535)GENERATE.Text n
 presentation.presented_at←'2005-04-03 00:00:00' '2008-05-05 00:00:00' '2012-12-12 00:00:00',GENERATE.DateTime n-3   ⍝ Fixed dates for testing date range filtering
 presentation.⎕DF'presentation'

 presenter←()
 ⍝ Using fixed keys in the presenter and presentation_video tables ensures that stems are found in video results for testing
 presenter.(presentation_id person_id)←fixed_keys←(1 2 3 3)(1 2 3 4)   ⍝ presentation 1 has presenter 1; presentation 2 has presenter 2; presentation 3 has presenters 3 and 4
 _NotFixedKeys←{⍺←⊢ ⋄ ~∨/,(⍉↑fixed_keys)⍷⍤1 2⊢r←⍺ ⍺⍺ ⍵:r ⋄ ⍺ ∇ ⍵}
 ⍝ FIXME not correct because ⍣ requires ←≡⍵
 ⍝presenter.(presentation_id person_id),←↓⍉{?⍵⍴⍛⍴n}⍣{(NotFixedKeys ⍺)∧∧/≠⍺}(n-≢fixed_keys)2⍴0
 presenter.(presentation_id person_id),←↓⍉{?⍵⍴⍛⍴n}_NotFixedKeys _Unique(n-≢fixed_keys)2⍴0
 presenter.⎕DF'presenter'

 ⍝ Videos is not a table to insert, but its data is used in other tables and must be consistent, so we create it here and re-use it below
 videos←()
 example_search_term←'wombo'
 videos.title←example_search_term⊂⍛,stems   ⍝ Unique keyword for search testing
 videos.title,←(vocab:lipsum ⋄ max:30)GENERATE.Text n-1+≢stems
 videos.description←(vocab:lipsum ⋄ max:65535)GENERATE.Text n
 videos.description[2]←videos.description[1]   ⍝ Guarantee similar video for recommendations test
 videos.youtube_id←↓{(⎕A,⎕C ⎕A)[?⍵⍴⍛⍴2×26]}_Unique n 11⍴0
 example_video←⊃videos.youtube_id   ⍝ Use example_video in DummyData.TestGETVideo

 ⍝ presentation_video links presentations to youtube_videos
 presentation_video←()
 presentation_video.(presentation_id youtube_video_id)←fixed_keys←(⍳6)(⍳6)
 presentation_video.(presentation_id youtube_video_id),←↓⍉{?⍵⍴⍛⍴n n}_NotFixedKeys{(∧/1<⊢/r)∧∧/≠r←⍺⍺ ⍵:r ⋄ ∇ ⍵}(n-≢fixed_keys)2⍴0   ⍝ Random unique pairs of numbers
 presentation_video.⎕DF'presentation_video'

 ⍝ presentation_media now holds free-text links (slides, PDFs, …) directly on a presentation
 presentation_media←()
 presentation_media.presentation_id←?n⍴n
 presentation_media.text←(vocab:lipsum ⋄ max:4)GENERATE.Text n
 presentation_media.url←GENERATE.URL n
 presentation_media.⎕DF'presentation_media'

 youtube_video←(
     youtube_id:videos.youtube_id
     title:videos.title
     description:videos.description
 )
 youtube_video.⎕DF'youtube_video'

⍝ All GENERATE functions take a right arg of number of records to generate
⍝ Left argument is max size of data (length in bits), OR a special left argument for specific settings

⍝ Tables are inserted in this order, so each FK target must come before its referrer.
 data←event_type event organisation person presentation_type presentation youtube_video presenter presentation_video presentation_media
